Reasoning: The claim is strongly supported by multiple high-quality studies. A randomized controlled trial (W2099054178, Credibility Rating: 3.2/5, Citations: 1212, Sample Size: 2946) demonstrated that daily oral ibandronate reduced the risk of new morphometric vertebral fractures by 62% (prop_165917) and clinical vertebral fractures by 49% (prop_165919). Intermittent oral ibandronate in the same study reduced new morphometric vertebral fractures by 50% (prop_165918) and clinical vertebral fractures by 48% (prop_165920). These findings are further supported by a review paper (25565901, Credibility Rating: 3.2/5) which also reported a 49% reduction in clinical vertebral fractures with daily oral ibandronate (prop_166800, prop_166986) and a 48% reduction with intermittent oral ibandronate (prop_166801, prop_166987). The consistency across these studies, including a large RCT, provides strong evidence for the claim.
